Which of the following statements about international law is correct?

Reference:Subject /Topic Area:HIV and the law. Constitutional law. Your opinion

The principal legal theory with respect to international law provides that all the States who have entered into an international treaty have an undertaking to make the treaty a part of domestic law either through legislation where the rights guaranteed in the treaty are enforceable in Courts.

To ensure that human rights are protectied in international law, most states have ratified a series of international status for example the ICCPR (International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights).

Another important source of international law apart from treaties is custom.

The Bindu Dharmasasana declared that natural laws were to take remarke of that all men were equal unless they were a hereditary class, in which case inequality was permitted.
